posts.Title: India vs Pakistan: What's the sound of one-hand clapping? Absent Pak fans dull buzz
posts.Author: Sandeep Dwivedi
posts.Content:
Indian supporters wave the national flag during a practice session ahead of the ICC Men's Cricket World Cup 2023 match between India and Pakistan, at Narendra Modi Stadium, in Ahmedabad. (PTI)

Thousands will be driving to Ahmedabad on the morning of the match. Over a lakh are expected to fill the stands by noon. At the stadium, there will be flags and chants. The periodic Mexican Wave too can be expected. But still the buzz that is associated with most India-Pakistan games will be sorely missed this time. The Pakistan fans, still waiting for their visas to be stamped, will be conspicuous by their absence.

posts.Title: Today in Politics: Congresss Madhya Pradesh first list on its way, Maratha activist Jarange to address rally
posts.Author: Express News Service
posts.Content:
The BJP has released four lists of candidates in Madhya Pradesh, fielding Union Ministers and MPs to shift the attention away from the anti-incumbency factor against Shivraj Singh Chouhan. Till now, the Congress has not announced even one list but that may change on Sunday.

The party on Friday held separate meetings on the Madhya Pradesh and Telangana elections — scheduled for November 17 and 30, respectively — in New Delhi. Following the meeting, Congress general secretary Randeep Singh Surjewala who is the central leader in charge of Madhya Pradesh said, “The people of Madhya Pradesh are very angry. Many scams of the BJP government are coming to light. Today, a tribal scam worth Rs 10 crore has come to light. On the first day of Navratri, the first list will be released.”

State Congress president Kamal Nath said the party panel had discussed the names of candidates in about 60 seats and would meet again. “A meeting of the screening committee will be held immediately after this. Only then will we finalise the list … we can announce our list on 15th (October) and the more discussion the better, because a lot of new things emerge,” he said.

As Anand Mohan J has reported, the Congress is trying to take advantage of factionalism within the BJP — mostly between loyalists of Union Minister Jyotiraditya Scindia and BJP veterans. It has also been targeting the Chouhan government over alleged corruption and hopes to improve its position among Other Backward Classes (OBCs) with the caste census demand and demand of quota within the women’s quota.

posts.Title: Jakhar says caught off guard: Shot in arm for Congress as several big guns announce ghar wapsi from BJP, SAD
posts.Author: Kamaldeep Singh Brar , Navjeevan Gopal
posts.Content:
The Congress in Punjab Friday received a major boost as four of its formers ministers, including three who had joined the BJP and one who had shifted to the Shiromani Akali Dal in the run up to the 2022 Assembly polls or soon after, announced their ‘ghar wapsi’. Two others from the Akali Dal, including a two time-former MLA and another who remained a legislator four times, also announced to rejoin the Congress.

Those who met Congress general secretary KC Venugopal in Delhi and expressed willingness to return to the party fold include Raj Kumar Verka, Balbir Singh Sidhu and Gurpreet Singh Kangar — all from BJP — and Hans Raj Josan, Dr Mohinder Singh Rinwa, and Jeet Mohinder Singh Sidhu — all from Akali Dal. Verka, Balbir Sidhu, Kangar, and Josan remained ministers in Congress governments.

Earlier in the day, Akali Dal expelled Josan and Rinwa for “anti-party” activities. Jeet Mohinder Singh Sidhu had resigned from Akali Dal Thursday, a day after party’s disciplinary committee served him a a show cause notice In a late night post on X, Congress’ Punjab unit chief Amrinder Singh Raja Warring said: “Various senior leaders from Punjab, including former cabinet ministers Balbir Sidhu ji and Gurpreet Kangar ji, former MLA Raj Kumar Verka ji, Mohinder Rinwa ji, Hans Raj Joshan ji and Jit Mohinder Sidhu ji… have expressed their desire to join Congress. They will be formally inducted into the party fold in Punjab”.

Jeet Mohinder, who had first won the Talwandi Sabo seat as an independent candidate, had later joined Congress and won 2007 and 2012 polls on its ticket. He had joined the Akali Dal in 2014 after resigning as Congress MLA, but went on register his fourth win in the bypoll held later that year. He, however, suffered successive defeats in 2017 and 2022 polls.

posts.Title: National Scholarship Test for UPSC CSE 2025: NEXT IAS aims to reward talent who cannot afford quality guidance
posts.Author: NA
posts.Content:
Every year lakhs of aspirants dream of serving the nation by appearing and qualifying in the Civil Services Examination but many are unable to succeed in cracking the examination. UPSC Civil Services Examination (CSE), one of the toughest exams in the world, demands adequate guidance, proper planning, and strategy. However, financial constraints have been one of the major reasons why thousands of deserving civil services aspirants are unable to get the right institutional guidance and education. Therefore, to support and guide such candidates in their journey of UPSC CSE preparation, NEXT IAS announces National Scholarship Test for CSE 2025 and rewards the talent who cannot afford quality guidance with up to 100 per cent scholarship on tuition fee for General Studies Pre-cum-Main Foundation course for 2025. 

NEXT IAS, an initiative of MADE EASY GROUP, is a premier institute for UPSC Civil Services Examination preparation. Within a short span of time, the NEXT IAS has established itself as one of the most preferred institutes for civil services exam preparation. Its experienced teaching faculty and comprehensively designed courses have helped many aspirants to achieve their goals. In UPSC CSE 2022, NEXT IAS had 7 toppers in the Top 10 ranks, 14 in the Top 20 ranks and 71 in the Top 100. In all, the institute had 624 selections which makes up 67 percent of the total selections UPSC CSE 2022. These toppers were enrolled in various courses offered by NEXT IAS.

The General Studies Pre-cum-Main Foundation course, one of the courses at NEXT IAS aims to prepare aspirants for both the Prelims and Mains stages of the UPSC CSE and help them gain a competitive edge for this prestigious examination. The course provides a complete preparation roadmap and is in line with the latest trends of the UPSC CSE syllabus. For aspirants who want to be part of the General Studies Pre-cum-Main Foundation course of NEXT IAS but due to unfavourable financial circumstances cannot afford quality guidance, NEXT IAS has announced the National Scholarship Test.

posts.Title: India vs Pakistan Live Score, World Cup 2023: Will India make it 8-0 against Pakistan in the ODI World Cup?
posts.Author: Pratyush Raj
posts.Content:
India vs Pakistan World Cup 2023 Live Score: It’s finally time for the most anticipated clash of the 2023 Cricket World Cup as Rohit Sharma’s India will lock horns with Babar Azam’s as the storied rivals lock horns one more time in the grandest of stages.

The Indian Express’ Sandeep Dwivedi, Sriram Veera and Devendra Pandey will be covering the game live from the Narendra Modi Stadium click here to check out our Cricket World Cup page. 

It’s going to be predominantly the battle of India’s batters vs the Pakistan pace battery even though the latter unit has failed to produce the dominant performances of yesteryears thus far in this edition of the World Cup. Against Netherlands and Sri Lanka, the likes of Shaheen Shah Afridi, Haris Rauf as well as spinner Shadab Khan has failed to click with Mohammad Rizwan’s gritty performance bailing the Men in Green out against the Lankans.

India, meanwhile, have started the tournament in blistering form with the likes of captain Rohit, Virat Kohli and KL Rahul all looking in good touch. The bowling contingent is also nothing to sneeze at as a buoyant Jasprit Bumrah and a wily veteran Kuldeep Yadav in hot form. Also, as Rohit indicated in the pre-match press conference, Shubman Gill, who was in doubt for this clash due to dengue, is 99% sure of making it to the playing XI which will bolster the team.

posts.Title: India vs Pakistan: Ahmedabad police asked to ensure spectators dont carry gutka into Narendra Modi stadium
posts.Author: Devendra Pandey
posts.Content:
The Ahmedabad Police have a serious task at hand during the India vs Pakistan World Cup game. Not only will they have to manage security and handle a large crowd, they have to even ensure that no fans bring ‘Gutka’ inside the Narendra Modi stadium.

Click here to follow all the action from the Cricket World Cup

The Gujarat Cricket Association (GCA) had specially requested Ahmedabad Police to ensure that no fans marched in with the pan masala or gutka as it creates plenty of problems during the game.

The masala chokes the bathroom pipe and results in waterlogging in its basin. It also makes the environment dirty and to keep it clean, GCA had to spend money on removing the stains. The state government last year had banned gutka and pan masala containing nicotine but it still found its way into the market.

posts.Title: Singhara, kuttu or rajgira: Which fasting alternative should you prefer this Navratri?
posts.Author: Jayashree Narayanan
posts.Content:
As the auspicious festival of Navratri is upon us, the spotlight turns to nutritious and gluten-free alternatives like singhara (water chestnut), kuttu (buckwheat), and rajgira (amaranth) as popular choices for fasting. Each of these grains offers unique health benefits, making them suitable for different dietary requirements. Understanding each of these food’s differences, benefits, and some popular dishes can help individuals make informed choices when incorporating them into their diet during fasting or at regular meals.

Singhara

Singhara is a powerhouse of essential nutrients and is especially beneficial for those with gluten allergies. “Packed with potassium, fibre, and vitamins, Singhara aids digestion and supports heart health. Its cooling properties make it an excellent choice for individuals with heat-related issues,” said nutritionist Dr Archana Batra who is also a certified diabetes educator.

Singhara flour is commonly used to prepare dishes like Singhara Atta Halwa and Singhara Paratha.

 Singhara ka atta can be used to make a variety of items (Source: Getty Images/Thinkstock)

How much to consume: Singhara is versatile and can be consumed in moderate amounts throughout Navratri. Incorporating Singhara into various dishes ensures a balanced and nutritious fasting experience, said Dr Batra.

posts.Title: Meta takes steps to remove Hamas-related disinformation
posts.Author: Reuters
posts.Content:
Meta said on Friday it was taking steps including removing praise and substantive support for Hamas from its platforms after the European Union reprimanded social media companies for not doing enough to tackle disinformation.

Since Palestinian militant group Hamas attacked Israel on Oct. 7, misleading claims and doctored images have spread on Facebook and other social media.

In the three days after the attack, Meta said it removed or marked as disturbing more than 795,000 pieces of content in Hebrew or Arabic.

Meta is also temporarily expanding its violence and incitement policy and removing content that clearly identifies hostages taken by Hamas, even if it is being done to condemn or raise awareness of their situation.
